article.headline: Baylor 77, Chicago St 59
article.story: WACO, Texas (AP) -- Tommy Swanson scored 19 points and pulled down 12 rebounds to lead Baylor to a 77-59 win over Chicago State on Monday. The victory was the fifth straight for the Bears (7-3), their longest winning streak since the 2001-02 season. Aaron Bruce added 15 points, Tim Bush 13 and Patrick Fields 12 for the Bears. Kevin Jones led Chicago State (1-9) with 15 points and Craig Franklin added 11. Trailing 35-22, Chicago State reeled off eight straight points to cut Baylor's lead to 35-30 three minutes into the second half. The Cougars pulled to within one point on three occasions, the last time at 48-47 with just under 10 minutes remaining. But the Bears went on a 12-3 run fueled by Swanson's seven points and moved in front 60-50 at the 5:49 mark. Baylor led by as much as 20 points at 73-53 with 1:30 remaining. Baylor scored the game's first seven points and extended its margin to 33-22 at the half. Bush led the way for the Bears with 11 first-half points.
